<br>
I was reading through varying threads regarding MA claws, but I still have a few unanswered questions that I either didn't see addressed, or didn't quite understand.  I tried some experimentation when teamed with some friends in a few missions this evening, but my results were very unclear.  I guess it's the newbie in me.<br>
<br>
In all these questions, please assume that I am only using one claw, as the data I read seem to suggest that using one claw/one fist is advantageous over two claws.<br>
<br>
First thing that confused me is this text that I found on www.red-tigers.com:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Martial Arts weapons are very interesting though, as they give you additional damage to your normal hand-to-hand combat damage. This means you should of course raise Martial Arts, Brawling, Dimach and Physical Prowess Initiative.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Does this imply that the claw weapon damage is generated and then added to whatever damage that particular fist would have done if I hadn't had a claw equipped?<br>
<br>
If this is not the case, and the claw damage replaces fist damage, how do we determine what our fist damage would normally be?  It's difficult for me to determine whether a claw would be better than my fist if I do not know how to tell how much min-max damge my fist does.  At my level (44), I was seeing my fists do around 120-ish damage or so.  Sometimes 80-ish and on occasion 50-ish.  Now when I had the claw equipped, my fist was still doing that much damage, but the claw would, on occasion, hit for as low as 30-ish to 40-ish.  I never saw numbers that low with just my fists.  Are those low numbers balanced out by an increase in the total number of attacks that I'm getting by dual wielding?  I couldn't tell if I was hitting more often just by trying to see how fast the damage text would scroll by.<br>
<br>
Also, someone mentioned quickly unequipping claws in order to use a special martial arts moves and then equipping them again.  Is there a way to rapidly do that, or will I constantly have to have my inventory/equipment windows open and manually do that?<br>
<br>
Basically I'm concerned because 1) I'm uncertain how much damage I should be doing at my level, and 2) I'm unsure how many IPs I should invest in piercing.  As I'm sure is the case with everyone, it seems as though I don't have nearly enough IPs to put into the areas that I feel I need.  Most of my nano skills are WAY behind and I can't cast several nanos whose QL match my level.  But that's another topic ....<br>
<br>
Any  help would be appreciated.<br>
<br>
--Dysdain <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maxiusmanaburn>Maxius Manaburn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~maxcool/usa.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 185<br> <font color=#660000>(2/17/03 9:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=517.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.bellatlantic.net/~maxcool/usa.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Answers</span><hr size=1> 1.<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Does this imply that the claw weapon damage is generated and then added to whatever damage that particular fist would have done if I hadn't had a claw equipped?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> No. You lose one fist attack and add one claw attack<br>
